&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Specialty Doctor Adult Psychiatrist – Community AMHS Hastings &amp; Rother 10 PA’s&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sussex Partnership NHS Foundation University Trust provides Mental Health, Learning Disability and Substance Misuse Services across East &amp; West Sussex and Brighton &amp; Hove. The Trust aims to realise the potential of everyone who uses its services and to enable staff to do a great job. Sussex Partnership has teaching status with close links to Brighton &amp; Sussex Medical School and is developing into one of the country’s leading Mental Health Trusts. Working with us offers continued professional development, variety and a rewarding challenge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to recruit a highly motivated substantive Specialty Doctor to work with Sussex Partnership NHS Foundation Trust with the Assessment &amp; Treatment Service in Hastings &amp; Rother, East Sussex. The post holder will work closely with Senior Managers and other consultants to contribute towards local service development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an opportunity for an enthusiastic and confident Specialty Doctor to join vibrant, dynamic and professional services. The Specialty Doctor will provide quality mental health care and treatment for patients with severe and enduring mental illness. It is expected that the post holder will embrace New Ways of Working in their clinical practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To apply please visit nhs jobs quoting ref number: 354-AE-20149&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameChristine HenhamJob titleClinical Operational Nurse ManagerEmail addresschristine.henham@sussexpartnership.nhs.ukTelephone number07887 982764Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Mohammed Ashir, Clinical Lead Consultant Psychiatrist, Hastings &amp; Rother 01424 726600 or 01424 776556&lt;/p&gt;
